Rating: 4
This was a fabulous dish. I did add some chopped seedless cucumber. Also used Israeli couscous and chicken broth instead of water for more flavor. I served this with the Moroccan carrots from this site, and the easiest most delicious lamb, from Oprah's February magazine. Recipe follows: 3-4 lb boneless leg of lamb, trimmed of excess fat,2 T honey, 2 tsp ground cumin, 1 T ground cinnamon, 1-1/2 tsp ground black pepper, 2 tsp kosher salt. Preheat oven to 400. Place a rack on the bottom of a roasting pan large enough to fit lamb. Rinse lamb and pat dry. Rub honey over entire surface, then combine spices and salt and pat into honey. Let sit at room temperature for at least 30 minutes (I did an hour). Roast 1 hour and 15 minutes or until medium rare (internal temperature should be around 135 degrees; for medium well, around 145). Remove from oven and allow to sit 15 minutes before slicing. Makes about 4 servings. The aroma when this is roasting is intoxicating...almost like an apple pie. I'm trying the same rub on a pork tenderloin this week. YUMMY!

