Rating: 2
I prefer my own recipe which I would like to share with you: After the couscous is prepared as suggested, the following should be added: First some lemon juice (not vinegar- lemon suits absolutely better), olive oil, salt, some chili pepper (the amount depending on the taste), one teaspoonfull of tomato paste (optional) and some mint should be blended in the fluffed couscous mixture while it is still warm so that all flavours will blend better. After it will cool, some thinly chopped parsley, fresh onions, sweet green or sweet red peppers, fresh mint-only a few leaves,all thinly chopped, should be added. Just before serving, some shredded (or chopped)lettuce leaves can also be added at the last moment, because the lettuce leaves are tended to lose their crispness if they wait long in the mixture. (Diced fresh tomatoes can also be added to the mixture as optional.)Bon apetit.